hands_on_practices.solution:
We start from the definitions in the shock-rest frame:  
$$h=j^2\Bigl(\frac{dV_2}{dp_2}\Bigr)_H,\qquad
j^2=\frac{p_2-p_1}{V_1-V_2}\,. $$  
For an ideal gas with $\gamma=\tfrac43$, the Hugoniot relation gives  
$$\frac{p_2}{p_1}
=\frac{(\gamma+1)V_1-(\gamma-1)V_2}{(\gamma+1)V_2-(\gamma-1)V_1}
=\frac{7V_1-V_2}{7V_2-V_1}\,. $$  
Introduce the compression ratio $x=\frac{V_1}{V_2}$ so that $V_2=V_1/x$.  Then  
$$\frac{p_2}{p_1}
=\frac{7-\tfrac1x}{\tfrac7x-1}
=\frac{7x-1}{7-x},$$  
hence  
$$p_2=p_1\frac{7x-1}{7-x}\,. $$  
The mass-flux is  
$$j^2=\frac{p_2-p_1}{V_1-V_2}
=\frac{p_1\Bigl(\frac{7x-1}{7-x}-1\Bigr)}{V_1(1-\tfrac1x)}
=\frac{8\,p_1\,x}{V_1(7-x)}\,. $$  
Next, write $p_2=p_1H(V_2)$ with  
$$H(V_2)=\frac{7V_1-V_2}{7V_2-V_1},$$  
and compute  
$$\frac{dH}{dV_2}
=\frac{-1\cdot(7V_2-V_1)-(7V_1-V_2)\cdot7}{(7V_2-V_1)^2}
=-\frac{48\,V_1}{(7V_2-V_1)^2}\,. $$  
Thus  
$$\frac{dV_2}{dp_2}
=\frac1{p_1H'}=-\frac{(7V_2-V_1)^2}{48\,p_1\,V_1}\,. $$  
Combining,  
$$h
=j^2\frac{dV_2}{dp_2}
=-\frac{8p_1x}{V_1(7-x)}\;\frac{(7V_2-V_1)^2}{48\,p_1\,V_1}
=-\frac{8x}{48\,V_1^2(7-x)}\;V_1^2\frac{(7-x)^2}{x^2}
=-\frac{7-x}{6x}\,. $$
Hence  
$$h=\frac{x-7}{6x}\,. $$
